section.section:
"Dialysis drugs and devices" means:
Dialysate and dialysis solutions;
Dialyzers, delivery systems, and their accessory equipment necessary to administer these products;
Heparin;
Local anesthetics and any other drugs and devices approved by the Board under subsection (g) of this section;
Needles;
Syringes; and
Sterile sodium chloride and sterile potassium chloride.

The Board may adopt rules and regulations to assure safe, proper, and uninterrupted distribution of dialysis drugs and devices, including rules and regulations as to:
Maintaining facilities that are adequate to assure proper security and control of dialysis drugs and devices;
Keeping records;
Labeling dialysis drugs and devices;
Receipts and returns from patients for dialysis drugs and devices;
Reports to the Board; and
Restrictions on specific dialysis drugs or devices, including limitations on the amounts that may be distributed.
